<li>Velasco G&oacute;mez, Ambrosio (ed.), 1997, <em>Racionalidad y
Cambio Cient&iacute;fico</em>, M&eacute;xico F. F.:
UNAM-Paid&oacute;s.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004, &ldquo;Toward a Political Philosophy
of Science&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy Today</em>, 48 (Supplement):
116&ndash;121</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, &ldquo;Rationality in Science and the
Arts: Common Sense and Heuristics&rdquo;, in <em>The Paths of
Creation. Creativity in Science and Art</em>, Sixto Castro and Alfredo
Marcos (eds.), Berna: Peter Lang, 71&ndash;80.
doi:10.3726/978-3-0351-0307-6</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015a, &ldquo;Rationality and
Method&rdquo;, in <em>The Routledge Companion to Hermeneutics</em>,
Jeff Malpas y Hans-Helmuth Gander (eds), London: Routledge,
251&ndash;266. doi:10.4324/9781315771854.ch19</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015b, &ldquo;Ibero-American Republican
Humanism and the Intellectual Roots of Mexican Independence&rdquo;, in
<em>The Traditions of Liberty in the Atlantic World</em>, Francisco
Colom Gonz&aacute;lez and Angel Rivero (eds.), Leiden: Brill.
doi:10.1163/9789004299689_005</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, &ldquo;Situational analysis of
Scientific Traditions: Popper&acute;s Hermeneutical and Political Turn
in Philosophy of Science&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Philosophical
Investigations</em>, 17(42): 127&ndash;139.
doi:10.22034/jpiut.2000.16577</li>

<li>Verdugo, Carlos, 2009, &ldquo;Popper&rsquo;s Thesis of the Unity
of Scientific Method: Method Versus Techniques&rdquo;, in
<em>Rethinking Popper</em>, Zuzana Parusnikov&aacute; and Robert S.
Cohen (eds.), (Boston Studies in The Philosophy of Science 272),
Dordrecht: Springer Netherlands, 155&ndash;160.
doi:10.1007/978-1-4020-9338-8_12</li>

<li>Vessuri, Hebe, 2000, &ldquo;Mode 2 or the Emblematic
Disestablishment of Science: A View from the Edge&rdquo;, <em>Science,
Technology and Society</em>, 5(2): 195&ndash;207.
doi:10.1177/097172180000500204</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, &ldquo;Science, Politics, and
Democratic Participation in Policy-Making: A Latin American
View&rdquo;, <em>Technology in Society</em>, 25(2): 263&ndash;273.
doi:10.1016/S0160-791X(03)00020-4</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;Crises that Mismatch Canons in
Science: Provincialization, Transnationality, Conviviality?&rdquo;,
<em>Tapuya: Latin American Science, Technology and Society</em>, 2(1):
26&ndash;31. doi:10.1080/25729861.2019.1586193</li>

<li>Vessuri, Hebe and Leandro Rodr&iacute;guez-Medina, 2022,
&ldquo;Producing Knowledge in Latin America: Social Sciences Research
Assessment with a Geopolitical Perspective&rdquo;, in <em>Handbook on
Research Assessment in the Social Sciences</em>, Tim C. E. Engels
(ed.), Cheltenham: Edward Elgar Publishing, 472&ndash;490.
doi:10.4337/9781800372559.00039</li>

<li>Villani, Giovanni, Elena Ghibaudi, and Luigi Cerruti, 2018,
&ldquo;The Orbital: A Pivotal Concept in the Relationship between
Chemistry and Physics? A Comment to the Work by Fortin and
Coauthors&rdquo;, <em>Foundations of Chemistry</em>, 20(2):
89&ndash;97. doi:10.1007/s10698-017-9293-4</li>

<li>Villoro, Luis, 1982, <em>Creer, Saber, Conocer</em>, Mexico D.F.:
Siglo XXI.</li>

<li>Wade, Peter, Carlos L&oacute;pez-Beltr&aacute;n, Eduardo Restrepo,
and Ricardo Ventura Santos (eds.), 2014, <em>Mestizo Genomics: Race
Mixture, Nation, and Science in Latin America</em>, Durham-London:
Duke University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Genomic Research, Publics and
Experts in Latin America: Nation, Race and Body&rdquo;, <em>Social
Studies of Science</em>, 45(6): 775&ndash;796.
doi:10.1177/0306312715623108</li>

<li>Zambon, Alfio, 2018, &ldquo;A Representation of the Periodic
System Based on Atomic-Number Triads&rdquo;, <em>Foundations of
Chemistry</em>, 20(1): 51&ndash;74. doi:10.1007/s10698-017-9297-0</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;Periodicity Trees in a
Secondary Criterion of Periodic Classification: Its Implications for
Science Teaching and Communication&rdquo;, <em>Substantia</em>, 3(2):
101&ndash;114. doi:10.13128/Substantia-502</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Chemical Reactivity:
Cause-Effect or Interaction?&rdquo;, <em>Foundations of
Chemistry</em>, 24(3): 375&ndash;387.
doi:10.1007/s10698-022-09430-1</li>

<li>Zambon, Alfio and Mariana C&oacute;rdoba, 2021,
&ldquo;Nanomaterials and Intertheoretical Relations: Macro and
Nanochemistry as Emergent Levels&rdquo;, <em>Foundations of
Science</em>, 26(2): 355&ndash;370. doi:
10.1007/s10699-020-09723-8</li>

<li>Zea, Leopoldo, 1943&ndash;1944, <em>El Positivismo en
M&eacute;xico</em>, Vol. 1 (1943), Vol. 2 (1944), Mexico D.F.: Fondo
de Cultura Econ&oacute;mica.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

